    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black Metallic. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies and a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission. The chassis is exceptional, with a verified-intact rear subframe and a high-pressure VANOS system maintained to exacting standards. It retains its factory-spec variable M differential lock and staggered forged alloy wheels, ensuring the original suspension geometry and turn-in characteristics remain uncompromised. Inside, the Nappa leather remains supple and free of bolster wear. This is a rare, investment-grade example for the purist seeking the pinnacle of naturally aspirated, analog performance.",
